. You can apply to join the testing program (or, once its launched, start using it &#8230; <a href=\"https://updraftplus.com/updraftplus-support-digitalocean-spaces/\">Continue reading <span class=\"meta-nav\">&#8594;</span></a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://updraftplus.com/updraftplus-support-digitalocean-spaces/\">UpdraftPlus support for DigitalOcean Spaces (storage)</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://updraftplus.com\">UpdraftPlus</a>. <a href=\"http://updraftplus.com\">UpdraftPlus - Backup, restore and migration plugin for WordPress.</a></p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7:\"udadmin\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:2243:\"<p><a href=\"https://digitalocean.com\">DigitalOcean</a> is one of the Internet&#8217;s biggest server infrastructure providers, much loved by developers, and has recently been looking to branch out into storage provision. You can apply to join the testing program (or, once its launched, start using it as an ordinary customer), <a href=\"https://www.digitalocean.com/products/storage/object-storage/\">here</a>.</p>\n<p>And the good news&#8230; they didn&#8217;t seek to re-invent the wheel and invent yet another protocol for remote storage communications. Their product uses the fairly-popular S3 protocol, which UpdraftPlus &#8211; both free and <a href=\"https://updraftplus.com/shop/updraftplus-premium/\">Premium</a> &#8211; already support.</p>\n<p>We&#8217;re on DigitalOcean&#8217;s testing program, and are happy to say that &#8211; it just works. Enter the correct settings, and away you go. <a href=\"https://updraftplus.com/use-updraftplus-digital-ocean-spaces/\">Here&#8217;s the guide to how to do it.</a> Just one thing to note &#8211; on the current UpdraftPlus release, you need to pre-create the bucket that you wish to use in your DigitalOcean dashboard. With the next release, it can and will automatically create a new bucket for you.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-228522\" src=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/spaces5.png\" alt=\"Entering settings in UpdraftPlus\" width=\"721\" height=\"306\" srcset=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/spaces5.png 721w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/spaces5-300x127.png 300w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/spaces5-510x216.png 510w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/spaces5-610x259.png 610w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 721px) 100vw, 721px\" /></p>\n<p>David Anderson (lead developer, UpdraftPlus)</p>\n<span class=\"et_bloom_bottom_trigger\"></span><p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://updraftplus.com/updraftplus-support-digitalocean-spaces/\">UpdraftPlus support for DigitalOcean Spaces (storage)</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://updraftplus.com\">UpdraftPlus</a>. <a href=\"http://updraftplus.com\">UpdraftPlus - Backup, restore and migration plugin for WordPress.</a></p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:69:\"https://updraftplus.com/updraftplus-support-digitalocean-spaces/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"2\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:42:\"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0\";a:1:{s:8:\"origLink\";a:1: