	(820,2,'2015-10-23 08:40:28','2015-10-23 08:40:28','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Grid4C announced today that it has been selected as a finalist in this year’s Fierce Innovation Awards: Energy Edition, a utility-reviewed awards program from the publishers of FierceEnergy and Smart Grid News. Grid4C was recognized as a finalist in the category of Big Data and Analytics.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Grid4C was selected as a finalist for its innovative, industry leading Predictive Analytics Machine Learning based software.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Finalists’ applications were reviewed by an exclusive panel of executives from major North American utilities including CenterPoint Energy, Duke Energy, Ameren Corporation, San Diego Gas &amp; Electric, Iberdrola USA, Commonwealth Edison, and PECO. Full profiles of the judges can be found at https://www.fierceinnovationawards.com/energy/2015#our_judges.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">All applications were evaluated based on the following criteria: technology innovation, financial impact, market validation, compatibility with existing networks, end-user customer experience, and overall level of innovation.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">“Being selected as a finalist for this prestigious award is a significant sign of the industry’s recognition of Grid4C’s market-leading algorithms and machine-learning based software to improve Utilities\' operational efficiency, optimize profit and increase customer engagement,” states Dr. Noa Ruschin-Rimini, Founder and CEO of Grid4C. “For this reason, Grid4C is deployed in a wide range of electricity markets, analyzing billions of meter reads from 3 different continents, producing more than 10 million predictions for utilities production and customer systems every day and transforming the way utilities interact with their customers,” she adds.</p>','Fierce Innovation Awards: Energy Edition Announces Finalists, Grid4C Recognized','','publis