	(836,2,'2015-11-13 08:03:12','2015-11-13 08:03:12','<strong>Direct Energy has acquired a New York-based energy management solutions company for $60 million.</strong>\r\n\r\nThe acquired company, Panoramic Power, supplies wireless and self-powered circuit-level technology with cloud-based analytics for energy companies. It has been partnered with Direct Energy since June 2014.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"attachment-266x266\" src=\"http://icv.dev/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/khanbadar-direct-energymg-300x170.jpg\" alt=\"khanbadar-direct-energymg\" width=\"515\" height=\"291\" />\r\n\r\nBadar Khan is CEO of Direct Energy, which recently acquired Panoramic Power.\r\n\r\nPanoramic\'s technology allows energy companies to gain information about device failures, energy-related infrastructure investment and real-time circuit-level consumption. It was recently named one of the top 100 Internet of Things startups by Forbes magazine.\r\n\"The commercial industry trend is moving toward more centralized energy management solutions with a focus on automated energy data collection and reporting, which is why Direct Energy aims to seamlessly incorporate Panoramic Power\'s technology and analytical\r\nexpertise into what we offer our growing customer base,\" John Schultz, president of Direct Energy, said in a statement.','Direct Energy acquires fast-growing solutions firm','','publish','open','open','','direct-energy-acquires-fast-growing-solutions-firm','','','2015-11-28 19:29:49','2015-11-28 19:29:49','',0,'http://icv.dev/?p=836',0,'post','',0),
