	(899,2,'2016-02-22 13:45:11','2016-02-22 13:45:11','<em>Internet of Things (IoT) in Utility Market by Software (Analytics, Security, Smart Grid Management, Predictive Asset Maintenance, and CIS &amp; Billing System), Platform, Service, Application, and by Region - Global Forecast to 2020</em>\r\n\r\nThe global Internet of Things (IoT) in utility market is estimated to grow from USD 4.63 Billion in 2015 to USD 11.73 Billion by 2020, at a Compound Annual Growth Rate (CAGR) of 20.4% during the forecast period. Currently, the IoT is at the center stage of digital transformation. IoT technology can bring exceptional operational efficiency to the utility sector. It can provide more visibility in the challenging operational environment, where the automation process can have a potential role to play. Cost efficiency, reliability, and safety are the desired goals achieved with the IoT application in the utility sector.\r\n\r\nThe report aims at estimating the market size and future growth potential of IoT in utility market across different segments, such as software, platform, service, application, and region. The base year considered for the study is 2015 and the forecast period for market size is from 2015 to 2020.\r\n\r\nThe research methodology used to estimate and forecast the IoT in utility market begins with capturing data on individual software market share through secondary research. The application of IoT in the three different areas of utility that are water, gas, and electricity are also taken into consideration to determine the market segmentation. The bottom-up procedure was employed to arrive at the overall market size of the global IoT in utility market from the revenue of the key players in the market. After arriving at the overall market size, the total market was split into several segments and sub-segments which were then verified through primary research by conducting extensive interviews with key people such as CEOs, VPs, Directors, and Executives. This data triangulation and market breakdown procedures were employed to complete the overall market engineering process and arrive at the exact statistics for all segments and sub-segments. The breakdown of profiles of primary is depicted in the below figure:\r\n\r\n<img class=\"attachment-266x266 \" src=\"http://icv.dev/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/iot-utility-market.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 266px) 100vw, 266px\" srcset=\"http://icv.dev/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/iot-utility-market-300x119.jpg 300w, http://icv.dev/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/iot-utility-market.jpg 600w\" alt=\"iot-utility-market\" width=\"542\" height=\"214\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Internet of Things (IoT) in Utility Market</strong>\r\n\r\nThe IoT in utility ecosystem consists of many vendors. The report highlights the key innovators who serve the niche segment of the market by offering out of the box technology. The key innovators identified for the IoT in utility market are Silver Spring Networks, Inc., Trilliant, Inc., OSI Soft Inc., C3 Energy, Energyworx B.V., Cryptosoft, Tibbo Technology Inc., Amplia Soluciones S.L., WAVIoT, and Grid4C.\r\n\r\n<strong>Target audience\r\n</strong>IoT Platform Vendors\r\nIoT Service Providers\r\nUtility Platform And Analytics Vendors\r\nSystem Design and Development Vendors\r\nSystem Integrators/Migration Service Providers\r\nConsultants/Consultancies/Advisory Firms\r\nTraining and Education Service Providers\r\nSupport and Maintenance Service Providers\r\nUtility Technology Solution Vendors\r\n\r\n<strong>Scope of the Report\r\n</strong>The research report segments the IoT in utility market into the following submarkets:\r\n\r\n<strong>By Software:\r\n</strong>Analytics\r\nSecurity\r\nPhysical Security\r\nCyber Security\r\nOperational Control\r\nSupervisory Control and Data Acquisition\r\nMobile Workforce Management\r\nDemand Response Management\r\nEnergy Management\r\nMeter Data Management\r\nSmart Grid Management\r\nNetwork Management\r\nOutage Management\r\nDistribut