	(1170,2,'2016-11-29 13:42:10','2016-11-29 13:42:10','<em></em>Scodix, the leader in digital enhancement solutions for the graphic arts industry, is riding a wave of phenomenal success coming out of drupa 2016. The company recently reported drupa sales have resulted in over 150 digital enhancement presses sold to printing and packaging service providers from just about every industrial country. Since pioneering the digital enhancement category in 2009, Scodix has been on the fast track upward. The company can now tout global installations of close to 250 systems in major printing markets worldwide.\r\n\r\n“As the established leader in the digital enhancement category, Scodix strives to not only innovate evolutionary new tools, but to continue to push the industry, as a whole, forward,” notes Roy Porat, CEO of Scodix. “Though we’re very proud of our unique and impacting technology, it’s about the success of our customers. The augmented service capabilities, broadened market reach, and new revenue streams created by Scodix digital enhancement systems simply enhance our users’ business attributes and pave a path of success. Drupa is proof the market values and appreciates the need for enhancement.”\r\n\r\nRiding high on its success at drupa, at Graph Expo in Orlando, Scodix featured Scodix Foil digital foiling station inline with the Scodix Ultra Pro. This popular configuration was recently awarded a Must See Em’ in the Postpress and In-line Finishing category, marking the third straight year (2014 thru 2016).','Drupa success wave flows for Scodix','','publish','open','open','','drupa-success-wave-flows-for-scodix','','','2016-11-29 13:42:10','2016-11-29 13:42:10','',0,'http://icv.dev/?p=1170',0,'post','',0),
