	(1351,2,'2017-08-10 08:05:52','2017-08-10 08:05:52','Scodix announced they are a recipient of a 2017 Printing Industries of America InterTech Technology Award. The annual Printing Industries of America Award recognizes technological innovation and excellence in the commercial printing industry.\r\n\r\nThe Scodix Ultra Pro with Foil digital press transforms a very time-consuming analog and expensive process that enables service providers and their customers to enhance their prints with vibrant foil treatments. Using the inline Scodix digital workflow, foil enhances any project in-house, who today have to outsource the foil application or to use a long and expensive make ready processes that include molds and dies.\r\n\r\nWith Scodix Foil, users can also apply variable data foiling. This is one application has proven to be highly profitable, enabling users to personalize each print. Either through variable names, as on collateral such as direct mail and greeting cards, or in variable patterns, allowing each sheet of foil to look completely different to the next, Scodix Foil ensures rapid ROI. For more information about any Scodix digital enhancement offering, go to www.scodix.com.\r\n\r\n“The judges were struck by the uniqueness of several applications on the Ultra Pro, such as its ability to produce braille text, crystals for product decoration, and dramatic holographic-looking 3D images,” said Jim Workman, vice president at PIA’s Center for Technology and Research. “The use of product enhancement for high-end packaging and marketing has developed rapidly, in large due to the ability to apply foil and other enhancements in a completely digital workflow.”\r\n\r\nPrinting Industries of America will present the InterTech Technology Awards at the 2017 Premier Print Awards and InterTech Technology Awards Gala (Sunday, September 10th) after the first day of the upcoming PRINT 2017 tradeshow in Chicago.\r\n\r\n\"We are honored to receive this award and proud of the impact Scodix Ultra Pro with Foil is reshaping our marketplace so quickly,” noted Scodix CEO, Roy Porat. “This Scodix innovative press has enabled users to realize the significant financial and marketing escalation, which is broadening their target markets and increasing their revenue. For our customers\' clients, it’s transforming an ordinary marketing project into highly revered, and in many cases, award-winning, giving brands heightened appeal.”\r\n\r\nThe Scodix Ultra Pro digital press is the most productive enhancement production system available. Engineered specifically for commercial PSPs and folding-carton converters, it efficiently produces tangible enhancements for a wide variety of applications, including marketing literature, stationery items, book covers, boxes and premium packages, greeting cards, photo albums with VDP capabilities based on a barcode system, and more.\r\n\r\nMaking the Ultra Pro even more impactful is the Scodix Foil Station, an optional in-line module that delivers unmatched foil enhancement capabilities, including high gloss and embossed, in a variety of densities for short to medium runs. Scodix Foil deploys a wide range of hot and cold industry standard foil films, coupled with a variety of substrates, including offset, digital, plastics, laminated/non-laminated, and coated or without applications for business and greeting cards, folders, book covers, brochures, labels, packaging and more. By applying this Scodix highly-advanced, highly-efficient digital process, commercial service providers eliminate long and expensive make ready (including molds and dies), making foil enhancement a truly profitable production center.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Scodix Ultra Pro with Foil Recipient of 2017 InterTech Technology Award','','publish','open','open','','scodix-ultra-pro-with-foil-recipient-of-2017-intertech-technology-award','','','2017-08-15 08:06:59','2017-08-15 08:06:59','',0,'http://icv.dev/?p=1351',0,'post','',0),
